content.thinking:
`bun.String.createUTF8ForJS` exists and takes `(globalObject: *jsc.JSGlobalObject, utf8_slice: []const u8) bun.JSError!jsc.JSValue`. This is much simpler to use than the `cloneUTF8` + `toJS` approach. And it properly handles OOM.

So my stringify will look like:

```zig
// Build output in arena
var output = std.ArrayList(u8).init(allocator);
try stringifyObject(globalThis, input, "", allocator, &output);


return bun.String.createUTF8ForJS(globalThis, output.items);
```

This is cleaner. Now I'm ready to write out the complete INIObject.zig file.

